28/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian police reported Friday (26 September) the arrest of a Serbia-Montenegro Army officer who has been sentenced for war crimes in Croatia.
Lieutenant Colonel Milo Novakovic was taken into custody on Macedonia's border with Serbia as he was traveling to attend World War I commemorations in Greece.
He is chairman of his country's Association of War Veterans.
A Croatian court in Sibenik sentenced Novakovic to 20 years in jail for committing crimes against humanity.
(AFP, FoNet, Hina, MIA - 26/09/03)
